The paper deals with the problem of detecting image forgeries using advanced image journaling tools, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The proposed architecture utilizes resampling features, LSTM cells, and an encoder-decoder network, which involves machine learning techniques such as deep learning (cs.MM), computer security and cryptography (cs.CR), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and machine learning (cs.LG). Therefore, these sub-categories are likely to be relevant to this paper.
